{"id":64210,"date":"2021-12-18T19:36:09","date_gmt":"2021-12-18T18:36:09","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=64210"},"modified":"2021-12-19T17:27:45","modified_gmt":"2021-12-19T16:27:45","slug":"wildlife-tourism","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/tips\/wildlife-tourism\/","title":{"rendered":"Things to know about Wildlife Tourism (+ better alternatives)"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2>Animal tourism to Avoid and Alternatives<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#x2019;s start off by saying that spotting what&#x2019;s wrong or right with tourism and animals can be difficult. Hannah and I have made multiple mistakes when it comes to this topic and this article is to help you avoid exactly what we have done wrong and the better alternatives there are. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-1080x752.jpg\" alt=\"wildlife tourism better alternatives\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"313\" alt=\"wildlife tourism better alternatives\" class=\"wp-image-71459 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-1080x752.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-800x557.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-450x313.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-30x21.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-163x113.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-259x180.jpg 259w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-768x534.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-1024x713.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-1440x1002.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-300x209.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-600x418.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24.jpg 1920w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-30x21.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034832\/wildlife-tourism-24-1080x752.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-1-zoos-aquariums\">1. Zoos &amp; Aquariums<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Many animals in tourism are living in Zoos and Aquariums. There is some argument that they are good for conservation purposes, helping to preserve threatened wildlife species. However, in reality, it&#x2019;s hard to decide if the benefits outweigh the negatives.&#xA0;Some reasons to avoid visiting zoos or aquariums:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Wild animals shouldn&#x2019;t be in captivity<\/strong><br>In captivity, they are unable to lead a full and happy life. For example, dolphins should be able to deep-dive and swim across large expanses of ocean. In aquariums, dolphins are kept in small pools that don&#x2019;t even come close to replicating their natural habitat.&#xA0;<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-587x810.jpg\" alt=\"alternatives wildlife tourism\"><\/noscript><img width=\"245\" height=\"338\" alt=\"alternatives wildlife tourism\" data-id=\"71376\" data-full-url=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16.jpg\" data-link=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?attachment_id=71376\" class=\"wp-image-71376 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 587px) 100vw, 587px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-587x810.jpg 587w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-435x600.jpg 435w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-245x338.jpg 245w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-22x30.jpg 22w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-118x163.jpg 118w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-130x180.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-556x768.jpg 556w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildlife-tourism-16-742x1024.jpg 742w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17182345\/wildli