r a charity like the Sea Turtle Conservancy in Costa Rica. Here they focus on researching, educating, and preserving sea life for the future. You could also participate in a beach clean-up and help make the oceans a safer place for aquatic life.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another alternative is to go snorkeling or get your PADI diving certificate so you can see the life underwater. Great countries to get your PADI certificate are <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Thailand<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/egypt\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Egypt<\/a>, and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/malta\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Malta<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--mustread \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--mustread\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Standard sunscreens pollute the ocean:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/tips\/reef-safe-sunscreen\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Use a reef-safe sunscreen<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-71446 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-819x1024.jpg 819w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-864x1080.jpg 864w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-1152x1440.jpg 1152w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-600x750.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21-24x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18033427\/wildlife-tourism-21.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-2-wildlife-sanctuaries\">2. Wildlife Sanctuaries<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Although some wildlife sanctuaries are doing a lot of good, there are many that are unethical. Any wildlife sanctuary that offers tourists the opportunity to interact with animals should be avoided. Even if you hear or see words such as <em>&#x2018;roam freely&#x2019;<\/em>, <em>&#x2018;conservation&#x2019;<\/em>, or <em>&#x2018;wildlife protection&#x2019;<\/em>, this doesn&#x2019;t necessarily mean that these sanctuaries are good.&#xA0;For example, some sanctuaries claim to save elephants from poaching but still allow tourists to ride them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n            <a href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\/pin\/create\/button\/?url=https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/64210&amp;media=https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18184050\/wildlife-tourism-better-alternatives-3.jpg\" class=\"block-pinterest\" title=\"Save this article on Pinterest\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n                <div class=\"block-pinterest__container\">\n                    <div class=\"block-pinterest__content\">\n                        <div class=\"block-pinterest__title\">No time to read now? <\/div>\n                        <div class=\"block-pinterest__subtitle\">No worries! Save on Pinterest to read it later.<\/div>\n                        <span class=\"block-pinterest__button\">Save<span class=\"visible-desktop\">&#xA0;to Pinterest<\/span> <svg class=\"icon\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-arrow\"><\/use><\/svg><\/span>\n                    <\/div>\n                    <div class=\"block-pinterest__image-wrap\"><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18184050\/wildlife-tourism-better-alternatives-3-19x30.jpg\" data-src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18184050\/wildlife-tourism-better-alternatives-3-376x600.jpg\" class=\"lazyload block-pinterest__image\" alt=\"Things to know about Wildlife Tourism (+ better alternatives)\" height=\"600\" width=\"376\">\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/div>\n            <\/a><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h4>Tiger Selfies<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>You may have seen or heard of tiger selfies in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/asia\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Asia<\/a>. This is an activity for travelers who want to fulfill their dreams of getting up close with these majestic creatures. In reality, it&#x2019;s not possible for a wild animal to calmly interact with humans and the sanctuaries drug them to do so. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Thailand<\/a>, in particular, is a popular spot for this kind of wildlife tourism. Many of the tigers are separated from their mothers from birth, confined in small cages, chained, drugged, and made to suffer extreme stress throughout their lives.&#xA0;Infamous wildlife sanctuaries, like the Tiger Kingdom, were even found to be selling tiger skin and body parts. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.vox.com\/the-goods\/2019\/4\/12\/18306590\/tiger-selfie-thailand-tiger-kingdom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Here&#x2019;s an article by Vox about this shady business<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14.jpg\" alt=\"Better Alternatives to See Animals Traveling\"><\/noscript><img width=\"270\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Better Alternatives to See Animals Traveling\" class=\"wp-image-71370 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1536px) 100vw, 1536px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-480x600.jpg 480w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-648x810.jpg 648w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-270x338.jpg 270w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-24x30.jpg 24w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-130x163.jpg 130w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-144x180.jpg 144w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-614x768.jpg 614w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-819x1024.jpg 819w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-864x1080.jpg 864w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-1152x1440.jpg 1152w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-300x375.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-600x750.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14-24x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180450\/wildlife-tourism-14.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h4><strong>Alternatives to Wildlife<strong> Sanctuaries<\/strong><\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Although it&#x2019;s hard to find wildlife sanctuaries that are ethical, there are certain databases you can check&#x2014;for example, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sanctuaryfederation.org\/find-a-sanctuary\/#usa\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Global Federation of Sanctuaries<\/a>. Make sure the sanctuary you&#x2019;re visiting works in conservation, is reputable, and doesn&#x2019;t allow any photos or touching of the animals. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"tropical bird wildlife tourism\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"tropical bird wildlife tourism\" data-id=\"71389\" data-full-url=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18.jpg\" data-link=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?attachment_id=71389\" class=\"wp-image-71389 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185429\/wildlife-tourism-18-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-