>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-3-wildlife-experiences\">3. Wildlife Experiences<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#x2019;s very common to see wildlife experiences on offer for tourists. This can range from walking with lions to feeding crocodiles or diving with sharks. All of these experiences can cause a variety of problems: upsetting the ecosystem, causing poor relationships between animals and humans, and putting undue stress on wildlife and the planet.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Crocodile Farms<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Crocodile farms give tourists the opportunity to feed the crocs, take selfies and even watch them in stunt shows. All of this is using the animal for entertainment and funding cruelty &amp; captivity of animals.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20.jpg\" alt=\"wild crocodile travel\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"325\" alt=\"wild crocodile travel\" class=\"wp-image-71393 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-800x578.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-1080x780.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-450x325.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-30x22.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-163x118.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-249x180.jpg 249w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-768x555.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-1024x740.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-1440x1040.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-300x217.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-600x433.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20-30x22.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17185453\/wildlife-tourism-20.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h4>Shark Diving<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Shark diving is another activity that&#x2019;s become popular with adrenaline-seekers. However, in order for the sharks to be lured to the cage, the tour operators use a process called &#x2018;chumming&#x2019;. This is where they put minced fish into the ocean in order to bait them to the diving site. Not only does this upset the ecosystem, but it can lead the sharks to associate humans with food. This can result in more aggression from sharks towards humans &#x2013; despite them being shy creatures.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h4>Walking with Lions<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Walking with lions is another tourist attraction, seen in places like South Africa. To make it safe for tourists to walk with lions in the wild, they remove babies from their mothers at a very young age and train them to be around humans. They also keep them in cruel conditions and teach them to replicate the behavior of domestic cats.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2.jpg\" alt=\"wildlife tourism lion\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"wildlife tourism lion\" class=\"wp-image-71457 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-109x163.jpg 109w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-120x180.jpg 120w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-512x768.jpg 512w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/18034227\/wildlife-tourism-23-2-721x1080.jpg 721w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.co