inourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-221x338.jpg 221w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-107x163.jpg 107w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-118x180.jpg 118w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-503x768.jpg 503w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-671x1024.jpg 671w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-708x1080.jpg 708w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-944x1440.jpg 944w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-300x458.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-600x916.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10-20x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180358\/wildlife-tourism-10.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure><\/li><\/ul><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3>Problematic to the ecosystem<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>What&#x2019;s more, wildlife tourism can cause problems within the ecosystem. Whether it&#x2019;s giving wildlife food outside of their normal diet, clearing forests to make way for enclosures, or bringing lots of tourists to natural areas. This can upset the natural biological balance and cause damage to habitats. <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Also read:<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/tips\/reduce-plastic-travel\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Easy Tips to Travel Plastic-free<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8.jpg\" alt=\"avoid wildlife tourism snake\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"338\" alt=\"avoid wildlife tourism snake\" class=\"wp-image-71357 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-800x600.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-1080x810.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-450x338.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-30x23.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-163x122.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-240x180.jpg 240w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-1440x1080.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-600x450.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8-30x23.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/17180335\/wildlife-tourism-8.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, when we went to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/malaysia\/langkawi\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Langkawi<\/a>, we saw tour guides encouraging tourists to feed the eagles chicken skin. This is not a part of their natural diet and causes an imbalance of the food chain and damage to the ecosystem.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><em>&#x201C;75 % of wildlife attractions have a bad effect on the animals &#x2013; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.tourismconcern.org.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/02\/Animals-in-Tourism-lWeb-FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tourism Concern<\/a>&#x201D;<\/em><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3>What can we do improve wildlife tourism?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We&#x2019;re lucky to have incredible wildlife on our planet, and, as humans, we should do our best to protect it. Luckily, there are plenty of ethical wildlife tourism alternatives that allow us to witness, protect, and preserve animals. These can be ethical wildlife sanctuaries that rehabilitate injured elephants and release them back into the wild or turtle conservation projects that need volunteers to patrol beaches.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><em>&#x201C;More than 550,000 captive wild animals are experiencing cruelty for tourist entertainment &#x2013; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.worldanimalprotection.us\/sites\/default\/files\/media\/us_files\/associated-with-cruelty-nov-2018.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">World Animal Protection<\/a>&#x201D;<\/em><\/p><p><\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip block-link--long\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">Tip:<\/strong> Raising awareness of the dangers of wildlife tourism is really important. Consider recommending a documentary to a friend, signing a petition, or taking part in a tree planting scheme.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"Animal tourism to Avoid and Alternatives Let&#x2019;s start off by saying that spotting what&#x2019;s wrong or right with tourism and animals can be difficult. Hannah and I have mad